genresAdvancedInfo.name: igbo traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Igbo traditional music is a genre of music that is deeply rooted in the culture and traditions of the Igbo people of Nigeria. It is characterized by the use of indigenous instruments such as the udu, ogene, and ekwe, and is often accompanied by traditional dances and costumes. The music is usually sung in the Igbo language and tells stories of the people's history, beliefs, and values.
